<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1038" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1038">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/4212.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister at
                                        Mexico City</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-10">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Silliman is still at Saltillo under arrest. Marchani, his clerk, left
                                this morning for Vera Cruz. Other Americans from Saltillo leave
                                to-morrow morning for Vera Cruz. They all confirm circumstances
                                attending removal of archives, money, valuables, code, from
                                Consulate by Mexican officials. Have made strongest representations
                                concerning release of Silliman and the restoration of code and other
                                property of the United States. Have asked that Silliman be delivered
                                to me and that he should be allowed to leave country under full
                                protection.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>